quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  13,32,"And already were [other] messengers ridiculed before you, and I extended the time of those who disbelieved; then I seized them, and how [terrible] was My penalty"
  13,33,"Is He who stands over every soul, aware of what it has earned (like others)? And yet they join partners with Allah! Say, \"Name (describe) them; can you inform Him of what He does not know in the earth? Or is it for their name´s sake only (that)"
  13,34,"For them is torment in the life of this world; but surely the torment of the Hereafter is more wretched still, nor have they against Allah a defender"
  13,35,"A similitude of the Garden which is promised unto those who fear Allah, beneath it rivers flow, its food is enduring, and likewise its shade (shelter, security)! That is the reward of those who fear (keep their duty); but the reward of disbelievers is the"
  13,36,"And those to whom We brought the Book rejoice in that which We have sent down to you; but among the clans (sects, parties, sections) are some who deny a part thereof. Say, \"I am only bidden to serve Allah and not to associate partners with Him; Unto"
  13,37,"Thus have We revealed it, a decisive judgment in Arabic, but had you followed their lusts (prejudices, fantasies, superstitions), after the knowledge that has come to you, then truly, would you have against Allah no protecting friend nor defender"